Job Description
Operator seeks to recruit a Drilling Engineer with previous experience. This role is based in Abu Dhabi and is offered on a contract basis.
Responsibilities:
Conducts necessary studies on new existing drilling technology, equipment/tools & programs, procedures and methods for necessary enhancement/improvement to secure efficient and safe drilling operations; Keeps abreast with recent development of new drilling technology, equipment/tools & methods/procedures; Proposes the usage of new techniques, equipment, tools and drafts methods and procedures as well as reviews & recommends amendments to the existing ones to improve operations achievements in economic /safe and optimum manner; Follows up and evaluates implementation of necessary recommendations of adjustments and/or trouble-shooting problems.
Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical/Petroleum Engineering or equivalent; Very good knowledge of English; Previous experience in drilling operations and engineering work including involvement in studies of drilling technology, equipment and methods.
Further details will be available to applicants who meet the minimum selection criteria for this role.
To apply for this position please submit your CV, in Word format, accompanied with your notice period and rate/salary expectation.
NOTES:
We will only reply to candidates who meet our minimum selection standards, therefore if you have not heard from us within 7 days, your application will have been unsuccessful.
Applications from candidates who are not authorised to live and work in the UK will not be considered and may be deleted.
Qualifications
Bachelors Degree Hons or equivalent
